cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.GT, cs.DS, cs.LG. 

This paper deals with coding theory, specifically cyclic codes over matrix rings and their isometric images over finite chain rings. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves algebraic structures and operations, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.GT (Discrete Mathematics) possible sub-categories. The construction of the non-commutative ring and the study of its properties may fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.LG (Machine Learning).
